-- BHP Billiton May Face Olympic Dam Delay on Approvals Process, Review Says
-- Rebecca Keenan
-- 2010-07-11T20:56:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-11/bhp-billiton-may-face-olympic-dam-delay-on-approvals-process-review-says.html

          
          
             BHP Billiton Ltd.’s Olympic Dam
expansion that could cost $20 billion may be delayed or crimped
by a protracted environmental assessment and the cost, the
Australian Financial Review reported.  
 BHP briefed the opposition party two weeks ago in South
Australia where the mine is located, the newspaper said citing
the party’s mining spokesman, Mitch Williams. BHP may not put a
proposal to its board for two years, it said,  
